# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Per-machine Docker Compose configuration.
#
# Docker Compose automatically reads a root `.env` file and honors
# COMPOSE_FILE, so each machine picks its own compose spec while everyone runs
# the exact same command: `docker compose up --build`.
#
# LOCAL machines: do NOT create a .env — with no .env, docker-compose.yml
# (the localhost spec) is used and everything works out of the box.
#
# PRODUCTION server (one time): copy this file to `.env` (which is gitignored,
# so the choice never gets committed), then uncomment and fill in the values
# below. See DEPLOY.md for the full runbook.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# COMPOSE_FILE=docker-compose.prod.yml

# Public IP or domain of the server — no scheme, no port (e.g. 203.0.113.10
# or todo.example.com). Baked into the frontend bundle and the CORS allowlist.
# SERVER_HOST=<SERVER_IP_OR_DOMAIN>

# Long random string, e.g. `openssl rand -hex 32`.
# JWT_SECRET=

# Strong password. Avoid `@ : /` characters — the value is interpolated into
# DATABASE_URL. Note: it only takes effect on first database init; changing it
# later requires updating the password inside Postgres too.
# POSTGRES_PASSWORD=
